{
  "stem": "17426.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 88.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "He organized a bicycle for me and we both went on bicycles to this camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And I went from barrack to barrack at night, like a church mouse, running in the dark spots where the lights would not catch me.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And go into the barracks and keep my finger on their lips so the girls would not scream, and tell them who I am and who I'm looking for.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Until I found my cousin, Balcia, who now lives in Toronto.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I just spoke with her the other day.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "She told me not to look around.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "That my mother and my sister, as did her mother and her sisters, and one of her brothers, were deported to Chelmno.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And there is no hope that I will ever see them again.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "She was right.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And when my mother reminded us at our deportation that we should come back here and meet all together, I thought of [? their ?] saying, when this is all over, we'll all meet here.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "We never met there again.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And so in early August, we had word about Treblinka, and Chelmno, and the Warsaw ghetto, and the uprising in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And we heard all these things from a resupply of inmates from the ghettos.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "But the story that they just took people in forests and just machine gunned them to death was very hard to believe.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Some of us didn't believe it, including myself.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "We couldn't possibly think that some element of people, who even if they hate Jews, could be that vengeful for no reason, really.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Political as it may have been, and whatever Hitler has accused us of, that they could do this, it was hard to believe.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
